ass=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/protecting-your-privacy-comprehensive-guide\/#8-use-passphrases-instead-of-passwords\" title=\"8. Use Passphrases Instead of Passwords\">8. Use Passphrases Instead of Passwords<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/protecting-your-privacy-comprehensive-guide\/#9-remove-hard-drives-from-old-computers\" title=\"9. Remove Hard Drives From Old Computers\">9. Remove Hard Drives From Old Computers<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-14\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/protecting-your-privacy-comprehensive-guide\/#10-turn-on-remote-location-and-device-wiping\" title=\"10. Turn on Remote Location and Device-Wiping\">10. Turn on Remote Location and Device-Wiping<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-15\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/protecting-your-privacy-comprehensive-guide\/#11-use-biometrics-as-a-means-to-gain-access-to-your-device\" title=\"11. Use Biometrics as a Means to Gain Access to Your Device\">11. Use Biometrics as a Means to Gain Access to Your Device<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-16\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/protecting-your-privacy-comprehensive-guide\/#12-use-a-two-step-authentication-process\" title=\"12. Use a Two-Step Authentication Process\">12. Use a Two-Step Authentication Process<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-17\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/protecting-your-privacy-comprehensive-guide\/#final-thoughts-on-data-protection\" title=\"Final Thoughts on Data Protection\">Final Thoughts on Data Protection<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-is-data-protection\"><\/span>What is Data Protection?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Data Protection is a collection of procedures and strategies used to secure data availability and privacy. It is one of the best ways to ensure data integrity. Some people may refer to data protection as data security.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most companies that store personal information about their clients and employees need effective data protection mechanisms. The best data protection method helps prevent data loss and manipulation and minimizes the damage that could be disastrous.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"principles-around-data-protection\"><\/span>Principles Around Data Protection<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Data protection principles assist in securing data while ensuring its availability. It involves actualizing data management concepts and availability. It encompasses all processes, from data backup to disaster recovery. Some of the key principles of data security include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The Principle of Data Availability: This principle ensures that users have access and the right to use the data to perform any business even if it is damaged or lost<\/li><li>The Principle of Data Lifecycle Management: It encompasses data transmission to offline and online backup storage.<\/li><li>The Principle of Information Lifecycle Management: This principle revolves around cataloguing, valuing, and protecting data and information from hackers and other disasters such as power loss, machine failure, user error, and virus attacks.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"why-is-data-privacy-important\"><\/span>Why is Data Privacy Important?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/importance-of-data-privacy-640x426-1.jpg\" alt=\"How important is it to protect data from intruders?\" class=\"wp-image-891\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/importance-of-data-privacy-640x426-1.jpg 640w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/importance-of-data-privacy-640x426-1-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Data privacy provides a proper guide on collecting and handling data based on its importance and sensitivity. <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/5-step-guide-to-secure-online-card-payments\/\">Financial data<\/a> is one of the most sensitive data that requires a high level of privacy. Organizations such as <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/\">Verv<\/a> that handle personal and financial data employ effective data protection strategies to prevent unauthorized access.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data privacy ensures that critical data is only available to authorized parties. These practices prevent hackers from gaining access to sensitive data such as emails, names, account details, and computer IP addresses that may ruin its integrity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, the best question to ask is: what are the best methods how to protect yourself online in 2022?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"how-to-protect-my-data-from-hackers\"><\/span>How to Protect my Data from Hackers<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"1-employ-data-encryption-methods\"><\/span>1. Employ Data Encryption Methods<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ibm.com\/topics\/encryption\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Data encryption<\/a> is one of the most common practices for ensuring online privacy and security. It is important to note that data encryption does not only apply to technological experts. Different encryption tools exist on the internet.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use these tools to encrypt information such as emails and computer files. These programs are compatible with different operating systems. They work through converting the data into an unreadable format. However, most encryption regulations authorize governments&#8217; access to data to help in an investigation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"2-employ-data-backup-mechanisms\"><\/span>2. Employ Data Backup Mechanisms<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It is one of the most basic types of data protection. Many people overlook this data protection style. This process involves duplicating all your data and storing it in a different location. It ensures that important data is not lost even after losing your device.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Almost 68% of small businesses lack data discovery plans. It means that they are at risk of huge losses if data loss occurs. Cloud storage provides an effective way to store your data. Unlike physical storage in a separate device, cloud storage involves keeping data offsite. Cloud storage guarantees data recovery in case of any data breaches.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"3-install-anti-malware-protection-software\"><\/span>3. Install Anti-Malware Protection Software<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Malware is the main threat most computerized systems face. Malware is simple software created to enter into a system and alter most operations without your consent. Malware resembles computer viruses, trojan horses, spyware, and worms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These files can attach themselves to emails or files such as photos, videos, or other freeware. However, not all freeware comes with malware. The best way to protect against the risks of malware is by installing an effective antivirus.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/5-step-guide-to-secure-online-card-payments\/\">antivirus programs<\/a> conduct frequent scans and remove any suspicious files from the computer. Most scammers user-friendly emails to lure you into the opening. Therefore, one should avoid opening any unsuspecting emails.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"4-update-your-operating-system-frequently\"><\/span>4. Update Your Operating System Frequently<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Updating your operating system might be a difficult task to perform. However, it is necessary to perform these updates to protect against any threats. These updates contain necessary security patches that offer protection against any virus.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Failing to perform updates puts your data at risk. Most software developers provide updates every month. Therefore, set your computer to update automatically once a new version is out.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"5-update-your-application-software\"><\/span>5. Update Your Application Software<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from updating the operating system, it is essential to update your application software. Most applications are set to update automatically to offer protection against any threats. Most of this software contains essential information that may put you at risk if you fail to update it.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"6-secure-your-home-or-office-network\"><\/span>6. Secure Your Home or Office Network<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the best ways how to protect your privacy is by securing your home or office wireless networks using a password. Hackers can access your system through the wireless network at your business premise or home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having a password prevents unauthorized persons in your proximity from using it. Some people may be looking for wifi access, but it is important not to share such information. Hackers also use programs that can display any wifi password. Therefore, it is best to encrypt and hide your network.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can hide the network by setting the router not to broadcast SSID.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"7-adopt-the-principle-of-least-privilege\"><\/span>7. Adopt the Principle of Least Privilege<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The principle of least privilege advises people not to log into the system using administrator rights unless they need to make important changes. Running and leaving your computer with an active administrator account could put you at risk of exploitation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Visiting unfamiliar sites through an administrator account can grant access to suspicious files that can enter the hard disc and delete all files.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"8-use-passphrases-instead-of-passwords\"><\/span>8. Use Passphrases Instead of Passwords<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Passphrases are a combination of random words or sentences. Cybersecurity experts recommend one to use long passphrases since they offer more data protection. It is easy to remember such phrases but hard for hackers to access your files.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"9-remove-hard-drives-from-old-computers\"><\/span>9. Remove Hard Drives From Old Computers<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Most people do not care about their old computers. These devices contain vital information within the hard drive. Therefore, it is important to make the hard drive unreadable before disposing of them. You can use different tools to wipe out any essential data from the disk or destroy the old computers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"10-turn-on-remote-location-and-device-wiping\"><\/span>10. Turn on Remote Location and Device-Wiping<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Tracking apps help locate your device if it is stolen or gets lost. These apps allow you to gain access to your computer and wipe out any essential data remotely. This action protects against unauthorized access to your data.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"11-use-biometrics-as-a-means-to-gain-access-to-your-device\"><\/span>11. Use Biometrics as a Means to Gain Access to Your Device<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Most computers and smartphones come with additional security features to prevent unauthorized access. Fingerprints are one of the most common tactics used to offer data protection. These devices store biometrics as mathematical formulas rather than the fingerprint itself.<br>Therefore, no one can access files without authorization.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"12-use-a-two-step-authentication-process\"><\/span>12. Use a Two-Step Authentication Process<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Two-step authentication provides additional security to any data if a hacker gets access to your passwords. The two-factor authentication will require one to input a second password to get full access to the data.<br>Some apps opt to send the second authorization code as a one-time password. These one-time passwords enable you to verify your identity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"final-thoughts-on-data-protection\"><\/span>Final Thoughts on Data Protection<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Online privacy and security should not be a one-time practice. Hackers are continuously developing creative ways to gain access to data. Therefore, companies and individuals should adapt ideal methods to ensure that their data is safe.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Despite these several security measures, most banks still fall prey to hackers leading to huge monetary losses. Cybersecurity is one of the main aspects that financial institutions should employ to protect their client information. <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/\">Verv online company<\/a> is one of the best companies that put data security at the top of their priorities.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{